Head of Finance
Williams Group
Dubai, UAE
Posted on: 6 May 2014
THE ROLE
Expand all
- Oversee and manage financial accounting and internal and external reporting for the entity by ensuring that appropriate financial systems, controls and processes are in place
- Manage 3 direct reports
- Monitor legal and regulatory requirements for accounting and reporting (in conjunction with with legal counsel) e.g. to ensure reporting in all required formats (tax statements, investor statements, etc)
- Participate in Executive Committee and give input on strategy
- Prepare budget forecast based on input from business units
REQUIREMENTS
- Minimum 10 years experience in financial services or banks, with a over 5 years in a senior managerial role
- Undergraduate degree in Finance or Accounting
- Preferred Chartered Accountancy qualification
- Strong understanding of Banking functions such as, Retail, Corporate, & SME
- Capable of assisting Business Units in setting relevant budgets
